[normal]Written evidence from the [bold]Public Administration Select Committee (PASC)[bold] (SCE0017)[bold]&#xa0;[bold]This note responds to the Liaison Committee’s 
[normal]short inquiry to follow up the recommendations made in its 2012 report into Select committee effectiveness, resources and powers.
[normal]&#xa0;[bold]Innovation and good practice[bold]&#xa0;
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]The Committee will shortly hear from members of the public with experience of complaining about public services, in an informal seminar, in order to inform its inquiry into complaints handling.
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]PASC work against core tasks (June 2012 to October 2013)[bold]&#xa0;
[normal]SELECT COMMITTEE CORE TASKS FOR DEPARTMENTAL SELECT COMMITTEES 
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]Overall aim: To hold Ministers and Departments to account for their policy and decision-making and to support the House in its control of the supply of public money and scrutiny of legislation 
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]STRATEGY 
[normal]Task 1: To examine the strategy of the department, how it has identified its key objectives and priorities and whether it has the means to achieve them, in terms of plans, resources, skills, capabilities and management information 
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]POLICY 
[normal]Task 2: To examine policy proposals by the department, and areas of emerging policy, or where existing policy is deficient, and make proposals 
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]EXPENDITURE AND PERFORMANCE 
[normal]Task 3: To examine the expenditure plans, outturn and performance of the department and its arm’s length bodies, and the relationships between spending and delivery of outcomes 
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]DRAFT BILLS 
[normal]Task 4: To conduct scrutiny of draft bills within the committee’s responsibilities 
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]BILLS AND DELEGATED LEGISLATION 
[normal]Task 5: To assist the House in its consideration of bills and statutory instruments, including draft orders under the Public Bodies Act 
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]POST-LEGISLATIVE SCRUTINY 
[normal]Task 6: To examine the implementation of legislation and scrutinise the department’s post- legislative assessments 
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]EUROPEAN SCRUTINY 
[normal]Task 7: To scrutinise policy developments at the European level and EU legislative proposals 
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]APPOINTMENTS 
[normal]Task 8: To scrutinise major appointments made by the department and to hold pre-appointment hearings where appropriate 
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]SUPPORT FOR THE HOUSE 
[normal]Task 9: To produce timely reports to inform debate in the House, including Westminster Hall, or debating committees, and to examine petitions tabled 
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]PUBLIC ENGAGEMENT 
[normal]Task 10: To assist the House of Commons in better engaging with the public by ensuring that the work of the committee is accessible to the public 
